{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"AnimationEnvironmentProxy"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/Motion\/documentation\/Motion\/AnimationEnvironment","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Motion20AnimationEnvironmentP","text":"AnimationEnvironment"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Motion extends common AppKit interface elements so that they can be used as animation environments:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSView"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSViewController"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSWindow"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSWindowController"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSApplication"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The AppKit types above are listed from most to least specific."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Prefer to use the most specific environment whenever possible to ensure the best results for your animations."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, if you’re configuring an animation inside of a view controller, you may use the view controller itself"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as the environment parameter for your animation:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["override func viewDidLoad() {","    super.viewDidLoad()","","    let anim = BasicAnimation<CGFloat>(environment: self)","    \/\/ ...","}"]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inline